==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oscinian
<hw>Os*cin"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of the Oscines, or singing birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oscinian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Oscinian
<hw>Os*cin"i*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of
numerous species of dipterous flies of the family
<fam>Oscinidae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Some, whose larvae live in the stalks, are very
destructive to barley, wheat, and rye; others, as the barley fly
(<spn>Oscinis frit</spn>), destroy the heads of grain.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oscinine</ent>⟦br⟧
